T*
(Running multiple nodes \(no host port conflicts\)) Tj
T*
(Use the built-in services; they run on internal ports \(P2P 56000, APIs 10100/10200/10250\) with) Tj
T*
(separate volumes. For more nodes, duplicate a service with a new name and distinct volumes.) Tj
T*
(Example addition:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Now run docker compose -f docker/docker-compose.yml -f docker/docker-compose.override.yml up) Tj
T*
(--build and both nodes run on internal ports \(56000/10100/10300\). CLI can target either by) Tj
T*
(setting ATHO_API_URL to http://fullnode:10100 or http://fullnode2:10300.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Exposing ports to the host \(optional\)) Tj
T*
(If you want to reach a node from the host, add ports: with unique host mappings:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Use different host ports per node \(e.g., 56001/10101, 56002/10102, etc.\). Then set CLI) Tj
T*
(ATHO_API_URL to http://localhost:10101 for that node.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Running the image manually \(without compose\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Configuring CLI target) Tj
T*
(- Internal compose network: ATHO_API_URL=http://fullnode:10100 \(default in CLI service\).) Tj
T*
(- Host-mapped ports: set ATHO_API_URL=http://localhost:<host_api_port> when running cliui.py.) Tj
T*
(- External bootstrap: set ATHO_BOOTSTRAP=<seed_ip>:56000 so docker nodes sync to your host/seed.) Tj
T*
(Use ATHO_RESET_PEERS=1 to clear stale peers on startup.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Performance-related knobs \(containers\)) Tj
T*
(- PoW worker scaling:) Tj
T*
(- POW_MULTIPROCESS_ENABLED \(default on\)) Tj
T*
(- POW_WORKER_CORES \(requested core count; runtime-capped to available CPUs\)) Tj
T*
(- POW_WORKER_NONCE_CHUNK \(worker batch size\)) Tj
T*
(- POW_PROGRESS_INTERVAL_SEC \(progress print interval\)) Tj
T*
(- Network/API scan controls:) Tj
T*
(- ATHO_MAX_MESSAGE_SIZE \(P2P message cap; defaults to consensus block-size ceiling\)) Tj
T*
(- API history/recent/balance caps are constant-driven and already bounded.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Security notes \(even for testnets\)) Tj
T*
(- API key + user/pass auth is required by default. If you expose APIs without TLS/HMAC,) Tj
T*
(credentials and payloads can still be intercepted/replayed. Set ATHO_API_HMAC=true and run) Tj
T*
(behind TLS/reverse proxy when publishing ports.) Tj
T*
(- P2P is plaintext/unauthenticated by design; firewall appropriately if exposed.) Tj
T*
(- Keys/LMDB data are stored on host volumes \(blockchain_storage, Keys, Logs\); they are) Tj
T*
(unencrypted. Use permissions and avoid sharing volumes across nodes unless intentional.) Tj
T*
(- Falcon CLI pinning is strict on mainnet/testnet; keep) Tj
T*
(Constants.FALCONCLI_PINNED_VERSION_DIGESTS current for the active consensus version before) Tj
T*
(deployment.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Platform notes) Tj
T*
ET
endstream
